<H3> <TI>   British Newspaper Alleges Nuclear Ambitions </TI></H3>
<H4>   Japanese Press Repeats Story </H4>
<F P=102> OW3101021594 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101021594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial report] Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 
31 January morning edition received via Nikkei Telecom Database, 
carries a 200-character report noting THE SUNDAY TIMES article 
on Japan's possession of nuclear weapons cited in second ref. 
The text of the NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN report, filed by London 
correspondent Yuzo Waki, is as follows: 
  "The 30 January edition of THE SUNDAY TIMES, an influential 
British Sunday paper, frontpages a report saying `Japan is going 
nuclear under the arms expansion race in Asia.' The report 
says: 1) The British Defense Ministry conveyed to the British 
Prime Minister's Office its concern over `Japan being forced to 
abandon its non-nuclear stance'; 2) a document submitted in 
January to the joint Intelligence Committee, the British 
Government's main security body, notes Japan has all the 
equipment and technology necessary for an early deployment of 
nuclear weapons; and 3) an expert who read the document said 
`Japan could have already acquired its own nuclear bombs, and 
all they would need to do is to select adequate amounts of 
plutonium.'" 

</TEXT>

