Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent; ITAR-TASS transmits a </F>
service message at 1542 GMT killing the following item] 
  [Excerpt] Rome, 28 Jan -- Viktor Chernomyrdin, chairman of 
the Russian Government, who is on a visit, acquainted himself 
today with the report from Tehran that Kazakhstan is changing 
its stance on the elimination of the nuclear weapons on its 
territory. Valentin Sergeyev, head of the Russian Government's 
press service, said this in an exclusive interview with the 
ITAR-TASS correspondent. 
  V. Sergeyev said that "the Russian premier expresses his 
doubts that the statement made by the Kazakhstan ambassador to 
Iran reflects the official position of Almaty. All the more so 
since Kazakhstan has not informed the Russian Government about 
such a change in its position. Viktor Chernomyrdin will have 
the opportunity to meet Nursultan Nazarbayev at the World 
Economic Forum in Davos, to which they have both been invited. 
Anyway, such issues should be resolved through talks with all 
the interested parties participating, including Russia, and not 
in a unilateral manner." [passage omitted: recap of Kazakhstan's 
ambassador statement on nuclear weapons] 

