<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Zlenko on Nuclear Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on Press Conference With Tarasyuk </H4>
<F P=102> LD0402192094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1415 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Kiev , 4 Feb -- At a news conference on 4 
February, Ukraine's Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko and Boris 
Tarasyuk, his deputy, discussed the Ukrainian parliament's 
approval of the trilateral statement by the Presidents of 
Ukraine, the United States, and Russia on Ukraine's nuclear 
disarmament. [passage omitted] 
  Anatoliy Zlenko said that Ukraine expects $4 billion worth 
of 
aid as a result of its disarmament. As regards nuclear arms 
withdrawal which, according to Ukrainian People's Deputy 
Valentin Lemish, seems to have started already, Tarasyuk said: 
"I declare with all due responsibility that no warhead has 
crossed the borders of Ukraine as yet. Indeed, three warheads 
have been transferred to Russia for dismantling, but only 
because of their disastrous condition and in response to 
experts' demands." 

