<F P=102> LD0802181394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1425 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802181394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Talks between the government delegations of Ukraine 
and Russia started in Kiev Tuesday. The talks will last for two 
days and are being held behind closed doors. The Russian 
delegation is led by special envoy Yuriy Dubinin, the Ukrainian 
delegation -- by Deputy Prime Minister Valeriy Shmarov. About 6 
agreements are expected to be signed following the talks. 
  The spokesman for the Russian Foreign Ministry, Yuriy 
Sergeyev, told Interfax-Ukraine that his delegation has a 
mandate to hold talks on nuclear weapons, the Black Sea Fleet, 
and mutual debts. 
  Commenting on the statement made by Dubinin that there are 
unclear points in Ukraine's stand on nuclear weapons, Sergeyev 
said that by its decision the Ukrainian parliament says "yes" to 
nuclear-free status. 

