Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoly Gordeyev] </F>
  [Text] Kiev February 3 TASS -- The Ukrainian parliament 
approved on Thursday President Kravchuk's actions during the 
January Russian-U.S.-Ukrainian tripartite summit in Moscow. 
  The parliament stated that Kravchuk acted "in conformity 
with 
the parliament resolution of November 18, 1993, `on the 
ratification of the Soviet-U.S. Strategic Arms Limitation 
Treaty'." 
  Under the Moscow accords Ukraine is to liquidate its nuclear 
warheads in exchange for security guarantees and one billion 
dollar compensation. 

