<H3> <TI>   Plyushch Briefs Argentinian Envoy on Disarmament, Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902141694 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 8 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "In Common Interests"] </F>
  [Text] Chairman of Ukraine's Supreme Council I. Plyushch 
has received Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the 
Argentinian Republic in Ukraine L. Baqueriza. A friendly 
conversation took place. The ambassador asked about the course 
of discussion by the Ukrainian parliament of the Tripartite 
Agreement signed by the presidents of Ukraine, the United 
States, and Russia and of the supplement on the elimination of 
nuclear weapons on the territory of our state. In the 
ambassador's opinion, these documents themselves and the 
decisions adopted by the Ukrainian parliament are historic. 
They, Baqueriza emphasized, have generated a lot of interest in 
Argentina. 
  Plyushch pointed out that we regard the Tripartite Statement 
and the supplement to it as a step of good will and as a step of 
good intentions on the part of Russia and the United States with 
regard to resolving this problem. All the more so since, in the 
course of preparing, signing, and adopting these documents, 
Ukrainian President L. Kravchuk acted decisively and correctly. 
  Touching upon bilateral Ukrainian-Argentinian ties, the two 
parties pointed out with satisfaction that the Argentinian 
president is expected to come to Ukraine on an official visit. 

</TEXT>

