<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arms Control Committee Concludes Meetings in Cairo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302211194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1920 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0302211194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 3 Feb (MENA)--The Working Group on Arms 
Control and Regional Security emanating from the multilateral 
Middle East peace talks concluded its meetings in Cairo this 
evening. During its five days of meetings, the committee 
discussed the two issues of arms control and regional security 
arrangements. It also discussed working papers and ideas 
submitted by Egypt and Jordan and a joint Russian-American 
working paper, a compilation of what was discussed during the 
committee's previous meetings. 
  The group also discussed a paper submitted by the 
International Atomic Energy Agency on measures to inspect 
nuclear weapons. 
  During the meetings, members also formulated a joint paper 
to 
be presented to Mideast capitals to form an official opinion and 
prepare for the paper's presentation during the meetings of the 
General Committee slated to start in Doha at the end of April. 
  MENA has learned that the coming meeting of the second 
working group will be held in Turkey during March to prepare for 
the meetings of the General Committee. 
  Some 19 countries, including the United States and Russia, 
will participate in the meetings of the Arms Control Committee. 

</TEXT>

