<H3> <TI>   255 Kg of Cocaine Base Seized in Guanajuato </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WB0020D Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 5 Jan 94 pp 
2-A-3, 4-A-3 </F>

<F P=103> 94WB0020D </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EXCELSIOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Ignacio Gutierrez A.] </F>
  [Excerpt] During an operation carried out in Guanajuato 
State, Federal Judicial Police forces seized 255 kg of cocaine 
base, with a commercial value of over 600 million new pesos on 
the drug black market. The narcotic was discovered in special 
compartments of a transformer stored in the packing department 
of a well-known freight shipping company. 
  In making the foregoing announcement, the Office of the 
Attorney General of the Republic added that the consignees of 
the drugs would soon be arrested. It is believed that this will 
have ramifications on the country's northern border, because the 
alkaloid presumably was to be sent to a construction firm with 
headquarters in that area. It was intended for subsequent 
shipment to the United States for sale and consumption. [passage 
omitted] 

