<H3> <TI>   Chamber President `Welcomes' U.S. Military Mission in San Pedro </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2901024794 Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2901024794 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The pro-government sector of the Colorado Party 
will reportedly oppose the coming of a U.S. military mission to 
carry out civil construction in San Pedro Department. [passage 
omitted] 
  [Begin Francisco de Vargas, president of the Chamber of 
Deputies, member of the Authentic Radical Liberal Party 
recording] I believe that President Juan Carlos Wasmosy 
initially agreed with the coming of the mission, but after 
pressure from military leaders who demanded Paraguayan 
participation, which was not granted, this project was 
obstructed. This is the information I have. I hope the permit 
will be granted to allow them to come. I do not see any 
unsuitability. It is said that the mission's hidden objective 
would have been the struggle against drug trafficking. If this 
is the case, I welcome it. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

